/*

Problem
Alice and Bob ran for N days.
On the i-th day:
Alice ran A[i] meters
Bob ran B[i] meters

On each day:
Alice is unhappy if Bob ran strictly more than twice her distance.
Otherwise, Alice is happy.
Bob is unhappy if Alice ran strictly more than twice his distance.
Otherwise, Bob is happy.
Your task is to find how many days both Alice and Bob were happy.

Input Format
The first line contains an integer T — number of test cases.
For each test case:
First line contains N — number of days.
Second line contains N space-separated integers — array A (Alice’s distances).
Third line contains N space-separated integers — array B (Bob’s distances).

Output Format
For each test case, print a single integer —
the number of days when both Alice and Bob were happy.

Constraints
1 ≤ T ≤ 1000
1 ≤ N ≤ 100
1 ≤ A[i], B[i] ≤ 100000

Sample Input
4
3
100 200 300
300 200 100
4
1000 1000 1000 1000
400 500 600 1200
4
800 399 1400 532
2053 2300 3400 23
5
800 850 900 950 1000
600 800 1000 1200 1400

Sample Output
1
3
0
5

Explanation

Test Case 1
Day 1: Bob > 2 × Alice → Alice unhappy
Day 2: Both happy
Day 3: Alice > 2 × Bob → Bob unhappy
Only 1 day where both are happy.

Test Case 2
Alice is happy on all days
Bob is unhappy on Day 1 only
Both are happy on 3 days.

Test Case 3
Alice unhappy on days 1, 2, 3
Bob unhappy on day 4
No day where both are happy → 0

Test Case 4
Neither exceeds twice the other on any day
Both are happy on all 5 days

*/

